cs.CV, cs.IT, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.NA 

This paper deals with image denoising, which is a common problem in computer vision. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses optimization techniques such as conjugate gradient, Nesterov, and heavy ball methods, which are commonly used in information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper involves numerical comparisons and speed-up demonstrations, which are relevant to multimedia (cs.MM) and numerical analysis (cs.NA).
